quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  6,82,"It is those who believe and confuse not their faith with wrong, they are those who shall have security, and they are the rightly guided"
  6,83,"These are our arguments which We gave to Abraham against his people. We raise whom We will by degrees of wisdom. Verily, your Lord is wise and Aware"
  6,84,"And We gave to him Isaac and Jacob, each did We guide - And before him We guided Noah - and among his seed, David and Solomon and Job, Joseph, Moses and Aaron, - for thus do We reward those who do good"
  6,85,"And Zachariah and John and Jesus and Elias, all righteous ones"
  6,86,"And Ishmael and Elisha and Jonas and Lot, each one have We preferred above all creatures"
  6,87,With some of their forefathers and their offsprings and their brethren; We have chosen them and guided them into the Straight Way
  6,88,"Such is the Guidance of Allah wherewith He guides those whom He will of His servants; and if they associate (for worship) anything with Him, their works would have been in vain"
  6,89,"It is to these We gave the Book and the Judgment and Prophethood. But if they disbelieve therein, then, indeed, We shall entrust it to a people who will not disbelieve. (See Matthew 8:11-12, Galatians)"
  6,90,"It is these that Allah hath guided, and by their guidance be you led. Say (O Muhammad), \"I ask of you no fee for it. Lo! It is naught save a reminder to the worlds"